The paper deals with the Maximum $k$-Cover problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem. The focus is on bipartite graphs, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The use of a purely combinatorial algorithm also supports this. Additionally, the paper involves approximation algorithms, which could place it in the Approximation Algorithms (cs.CC) or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental analysis of the algorithm suggests that it may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
